<TD align="left"><pre>


<strong><u>Automatic:</u></strong>

The auto variables stored in memory
Its default initial value is garbage value.
Scope of the variable is with in the function in which it is declared/defined.
Lifetime: Till the control remains in the block in which the variable is defined.

ex1:          main()
                 {
	auto int x,y;
	printf("%d" \t %d", x,y);
                 }
 Output: Some garbage values we get
        St different times of running this program, we can get different outputs.

To examine scope and lifetime of variable (auto)

Ex: 
	main()
	{
	auto int i=1;
	{
	auto int i=2;
	{
	auto int i=3;
	printf("%d \n", i);
	}
	printf("%d \n", i);
	}
	printf("%d \n", i);
	}

Output: 3
             2
             1



